1 §1432. Louisiana Real Estate Commission; qualifications; terms of office
2 A. The Louisiana Real Estate Commission is hereby created within the office
3 of the governor. The commission shall consist of eleven members appointed by the
4 governor. One member shall be appointed from each of the seven supreme court
5 districts. Two members shall be appointed at large. Two members shall be
6 appointed from the following districts: one appointee from either the Fourth
7 Congressional District or the Fifth Congressional District and one appointee from
8 either the First, Second, Third, or Sixth Congressional District. One member shall
9 be appointed from each congressional district, and the remaining members shall be
10 appointed at large. Each appointment by the governor shall be submitted to the
11 Senate for confirmation.
